headline: Mélenchon accused of antisemitism after 'Epstein' pronunciation comments
description: The leader of LFI later called his remark 'ironic' and accused rivals of 'inciting violence' against his party.

headline: Pakistan and Afghanistan escalate conflict, with unpredictable consequences
EU to provisionally apply Mercosur trade deal while awaiting top court approval
Former Elysée Palace steward on trial for stealing precious porcelain
description: Three men appeared Thursday before Paris's criminal court for stealing or possessing more than 100 pieces from the tableware collection of the presidential palace.

headline: 2026 Césars: 'L'Attachement,' 'Nouvelle Vague,' Léa Drucker and Laurent Lafitte honored at French film awards
description: No single film dominated the votes, though the 'Nouvelle Vague' biopic about the early days of Jean-Luc Godard took home four statuettes: best director for Richard Linklater, best editing, best costumes, and best cinematography.

headline: Could Punch the monkey make us a little more human?
description: Social media users around the world are captivated by the plight of a baby monkey abandoned by its mother and taken in by a Japanese zoo. The story reveals how our tendency toward anthropomorphism can spark a rare, collective empathy.

headline: Ukraine: 'The war could still last for years and paradoxically, time is not on the Kremlin's side'
description: Researcher Dimitri Minic tells Le Monde in an interview that it is 'too soon to write off Ukraine,' even though the balance of power currently favors Russia.

How Paris is turning into 'Frollywood,' a refuge for American actors
description: Whether George Clooney, Matt Dillon or Kristen Stewart, France is attracting more and more actors from across the Atlantic. This trend speaks to both the Trump-era crisis and the decline of the Hollywood model.

headline: Four years of war in Ukraine: Five photographers on assignment for Le Monde share their most striking images from 2025
description: Five photographers who covered the conflict in 2025 have each chosen an emblematic image of the conflict. Beyond the official figures and statements, these unique perspectives reveal the mark that this new year of war has left on them.

headline: 'The unnatural alliance between Trump and White evangelicals has cost them dearly, even if it allowed them to gain positions of power'
description: Historian Sébastien Fath discusses the history and dynamics of evangelical Protestant churches in an interview with Le Monde. Despite their current vibrancy, their growth is not inevitable, the researcher argues.

headline: 'The Epstein scandal is astonishing by the scale of the complicity and rape culture at the top of society'
